  "text": "It has long been accepted that telomerase is down-regulated in all but a few progenitor cell lines and furthermore, the reactivation of telomerase is responsible for the immortality associated with cancer cells [CITATION_1] . The addition of telomeric DNA by telomerase in cancer cells is thought to be a major cause in maintaining the indefinite proliferation of cancer cells.",
